ce:section.ce:para:
To further examine the ORR performance of the synthesized electrocatalysts, LSV measurements were performed on GC in an O2-saturated 0.1 mol L−1 KOH solution (Fig. 8
                     ). The ORR onset potential of the MOF-T3 catalyst is around 0.68 V, and at 1600 rpm, the limiting current density is achieved at 4.27 mA cm−2. Regarding those of MOF-T1, and MOF-T2, respectively, a positive shift of the onset potential of 50 mV and 65 mV and a decrease in the limiting current density of 2.7 mA cm−2 and 1.8 mA cm−2 are found. Additionally, the MOF-T3 catalyst's ORR performance is comparable to that of the benchmark Pt/C catalyst (limiting current density of 4.6 mA cm−2) and ORR onset-potential of 0.74 V. As a result, the MOF-T3 shows a Tafel slope (54 mV/dec) close to Pt/C (47 mV/dec), and lower than the MOF-T2 (84 mV/dec), and MOF-T1 (154 mV/dec) (Fig. 8 inset), demonstrating a faster rate-determined step for ORR. In addition, the OER and ORR of the prepared MOF-T3 exhibits suprier performance than most electrocatalysts reported in Table 1
                     , even despite having a lower loading.
